As part of efforts to cushion the sufferings of his constituents in the fasting month of Ramadan, Senator Ibrahim Mohammed Bomai representing Yobe South senatorial district has today launched the distribution of foodstuffs and cash. Abubakar MB Tamana one of the legislative aides to the Lawmaker revealed to Daily Independent at one of the distribution points. According to him “1,306 party stalwarts across Yobe Southwill benefit from the foodstuffs mostly rice and a cash between the sum of N20,000 to N50,000 Ramadan cash gift”. Tamana said that the constituents in the four local government areas of Fune, Fika, Potiskum and Nangere will all benefit from the gesture adding that “we also do similar to the Christian faithful during the Christmas season, the senator is an all-inclusive senator who carries everyone irrespective of any difference”. He further enjoyed the Muslims to use the fasting period to forgive one another, pray for the peace and unity of the zone and state nation and to help the downtrodden among them as it is enshrined in Islam.